		"notes": "\n\t<p><i>With smoldering hides the color and texture of burnt charcoal, these volcano-born trolls radiate relentless waves of furnace-like heat.</i></p>\n\t<p></p>\n\t<p><strong>AC</strong> 12, <strong>HP</strong> 33, <strong>ATK</strong> 2 claw +7 (1d6) and 1 bite +7 (1d10), <strong>MV</strong> near, <strong>S</strong> +3, <strong>D</strong> +1, <strong>C</strong> +2, <strong>I</strong> -1, <strong>W</strong> +0, <strong>Ch</strong> -1, <strong>AL</strong> <strong>C</strong>, <strong>LV</strong> 8</p><p></p>\n\t<p><strong>Living Furnace</strong>. Creatures within close range of a magma troll take 1d6 damage at the start of their turn. Non-magical metal objects that touch a magma troll melt on a d6 roll of 1-3.</p><p></p><p><strong>Regenerate</strong>. Regains 2d6 HP on turn unless its wounds are cauterized with acid.</p><p></p><p><strong>Volcano-born</strong>. Fire immune. Double damage from cold attacks.</p><p></p>",
